# Backend Architecture Rules

- Controllers handle request/response concerns only.
- Services hold business rules, orchestration, and error decisions.
- DTOs validate input with class-validator.
- Entities model persistence; transformers shape output when needed.
- Use modules to compose features and keep dependencies explicit.
- Put shared guards, decorators, filters, strategies, exceptions, and validators in `src/common`.
- Keep Swagger decorators and endpoint contracts aligned with the implemented behavior.
- Prefer structured domain errors over ad hoc thrown strings.
